				<p class="headerDashlet">Glodyne Connexion</p>
				<p class="blacklink">In today s business world
				a companys employees are its most valuable resource.
				We are familiar with the symptoms of work pressure handled by each
				individual in our every day schedule. The approach of FUN @
				workplace is a way to connect employee relationship overcome regular
				work and refresh minds to accelerate productivity.</p>
				<p class="blacklink">Glodyne Connexions is part of employee
				engagement activities. It is an initiative to Involve members with
				Innovate thoughts and Inspire them towards their workplace. Glodyne
				Connexions is committed in their efforts to help across organization
				achieve lasting improvements in their workplace relationships.</p>
				<p class="blacklink">A group committee is formed to initiate
				monthly activities to create fun at work. Employees are enthusiastic
				and passionate about their work and the company's mission. In a
				high-trust environment people cooperate and collaborate leading to
				positive workplace interactions higher profits and greater
				productivity.</p>

				<p class="blacklink">Some of the activities listed under Glodyne Connexion are:
				
				<span class="orange"><strong><p>1. Painting
				Competition:</p></strong></span></p>
				<p><span class="blacklink">Painting is the art in which
				colors and lines make a visual impression. Painting can be fun its a
				mode of expression and the forms are numerous. Drawing composition
				or abstraction and other aesthetics may serve to manifest the
				expressive and conceptual intention of the practitioner. 
				
				The competition offers participants a chance to showcase their
				creativity painting skills as well as on a company front helps
				enhance the employee creativity provides a platform to showcase
				personal hobby. </span>
				
				<span class="orange"><strong><p>2. Quiz Competition</p></strong></span>
				
				<span class="blacklink">A quiz is a form of game or mind
				sport in which the players (as individuals or in teams) are assessed
				in current affairs General Knowledge and similar fields to measure
				growth in knowledge abilities and/or skills.
				
				The competition offers participants a chance to work in team
				showcase their talent skills and get a higher competitive edge. On a
				company front it helps enhance the employee knowledge bank overall
				current updates of the industry. </span></p>
				<p><span class="orange"><strong> 3. Blood
				Donation camp</strong></span>
				
				<span class="blacklink">Blood is the part of life that is
				given to those who need it by those who have the resource to satisfy
				the need. The love of fellow human and a desire to share something
				of oneself is what singles out a blood donor from the others.
				Emergencies occur every minute. </span></p>
				<p class="blacklink">The camp offers participants a chance to
				work towards the wellbeing of the society. On a company front it is
				a part of the corporate social responsibility also an initiative to
				create social awareness. Lets pledge our self and contribute our bit
				towards this noble cause. Our Blood Donation can save a life!</p>
				<p>
				<span class="orange"><strong> 4. Independence Day
				Celebration</strong></span>
				
				<span class="blacklink"> A moment comes which comes but
				rarely in history when we step out from the old to the new India
				discovers herself again. J.L.Nehru On the eve of Indias independence
				we celebrated the 64th Independence Day across locations and with a
				same patriotic spirit </span></p>
				<p><span class="blacklink">All offices played the
				National Anthem at sharp 11AM. The entire office was dressed in the
				tri colors of patriotism. 
				With a common objective to share the feeling of loyalty and the
				dedication of all our freedom fighters this day was celebrated
				across with great enthusiasm and delight.</span> 
				</p>
				<p class="orange"><strong> 5. Diwali Celebration</strong></p>
				<p class="blacklink">Each year on the dawn of Ammavaasa in the
				month Kartik the glittering diyas the dazzling fireworks sounds of
				crackers announces the arrival of the most vibrant festival of
				India-Diwali. The word Diwali has its origin in the Sanskrit word
				Deepavali which means rows of light. This 5 day long Hindu festival
				is celebrated throughout the world with great zeal and fanaticism</p>
				<p><span class=blacklink>At Glodyne diwali festival was
				celebrated on a grand scale with fun activities and games. The
				entire office was decorated with vibrant colors and a token of
				appreciation was presented to all Glodyners. </span>
				</p>
				<p class=orange><strong>6. Friendship day Celebration</strong></p>
				<p class=blacklink>Friendship Day celebrations take place on the
				first Sunday of August every year. The tradition of dedicating a day
				in honor of friends began in US in 1935. Gradually the festival
				gained popularity and today Friendship Day is celebrated in large
				number of countries including India.</p>
				<p class=blacklink>At Glodyne as part of a employee engagement
				initiative we celebrated Friendship Day across locations. We kept
				wrist band of all colors for all the employees some games like
				Housie etc were arranged.</p>
				<p class=orange><strong>7. Glo- Feast</strong></p>
				<p class="blacklink">Feast is a meal that is well
				prepared and greatly enjoyed. 
				
				We at Glodyne often share times together in groups to enhance better
				team building among departments.
				This December we planned an event called Glo Feast where all the
				members across offices enjoyed their lunch together. Everyone
				contributed with a small taste of their religion and the entire
				gamut of regional food stuffs were collectively served and enjoyed
				by all.</p>
				<p><span class=blacklink>Goldyne Connexions helps in
